<h1>Pie Crust</h1>

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>Makes 2 large pie crusts</p>

<h2>Ingredients</h2>

<ul>
<li>3 cups flour</li>
<li>1.5 tsp salt</li>
<li>2/3 Cups shorting</li>
<li>.5 cup cold butter (almost frozen)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Instructions</h2>

<ul>
<li>Mix flour and salt</li>
<li>Grate the cold butter and cut into flour mixture</li>
<li>Cut in the shortning</li>
<li>Should have a crumbly mixture with pieces the size a pea</li>
<li>Sprinkle water in (~6 tbsp)</li>
<li>Try to make a doe ball. Once you can, roll it</li>
<li>If it gets too warm, put back in fridge</li>
</ul>
